    "key_notes": "Formation 4-3-1-2. Dick Advocaat keeps the same XI from the 7-1 loss to Germany (June 14, Houston); no injury withdrawals reported. Zero points after MD1; elimination is virtually certain with another loss. Morale is visibly depressed after the historic thrashing — emotional_state_today capped below 85 for all players. The exception is Livano Comenencia (22), who scored Curacao's first-ever World Cup goal vs Germany (deflected finish, 21') — his motivation and emotional state today are the highest on the squad. Riechedly Bazoer (CB) carries the lowest confidence today: he conceded the penalty that made it 3-1 (foul on Nmecha) and deflected a Havertz shot for the corner that led to Schlotterbeck's goal — two direct errors in one match; discipline and composure_volatility reflect this. Armando Obispo (PSV) was Curacao's most composed defender vs Germany and is the defensive anchor; he gets the highest skill and consistency of the back four. Tahith Chong (Sheffield United, born in Willemstad) and Comenencia rated 7/10 in the Germany match — they are the two most dangerous attacking outlets. Leandro Bacuna (cap 71, 34 years old) is captain and deep creative hub; reduced pace and stamina_base reflect age. Juninho Bacuna contributes pressing energy and 14 intl goals worth of finishing instinct. Sontje Hansen plays as second striker / wide forward — raw pace (top speed 34 km/h) is his main weapon; limited experience at this level (limited caps). Eloy Room (37) was credited with 4 saves vs Germany but conceded 7; confidence slightly dented but experience keeps composure_mean stable. Tactical context: Advocaat will set up compact 4-3-1-2, sit deep, prioritize defensive shape, and look for Chong and Hansen on fast breaks. Ecuador are heavy favorites and need a win. Risk of another multi-goal concession is real if Bazoer commits another error. No suspensions. No players on yellow-card accumulation cutoff. Venue: Arrowhead Stadium, Kansas City (neutral for both sides). Kickoff: 8:00 PM ET, June 20 2026."
